  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "release is launched by a maintainer (npm run release on master).\n\nonce pushed to master, travis do the hard job (and run the test again for safety).\n\n> How do you wait for the release to be available?\n\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/master/scripts/finish-release.sh#L12-L24\n\n> Also, how long does it usually take?\n\nBetween one and 30 minutes, depends on the jsdelivr bot (also is it's just a website update, not a new release, then it's immediate).\n\nwe do not use the gh-pages build on travis because travis won't launch any build of gh-pages.\n\nSo on master, we just push to gh pages and then right away update the search index\n",
